http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/Duo-held-for-car-thefts/article13984895.ece

Two cousins named Karan and Arjun have been arrested for a series of automobile thefts in the national Capital, police said.CCTV footage about one such theft helped police in identifying them.With this, seven stolen vehicles, including a Honda City car, have been recovered. Karan and Arjun are 22 and 18 years old respectively, said Vijay Singh, DCP (North-West).The duo was arrested after police at the Adarsh Nagar police station were tipped off about them being in the area on a stolen motorcycle.Interrogation revealed that the suspects used a master key to unlock the vehicles.